      Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukhumak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/02 12:56:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something Warriors should be worried about...</span><hr size=1> I think what warriors have more to worry about is the fact that the better buffs will further reduce the HP advantage we have over other classes on a percentage basis.  Unless they put in a change that gives us a tanking advantage that we retain on a proportional basis as gear and buffs scale up to endgame level we will be further marginalized.<br>
<br>
The difference is already fairly small with 8000 hp warriors and 7500 hp knights possible.  Imagine a raid with a 13000 hp warrior and a 12500 hp paladin, or a 11500 hp monk.    No way the warrior would be tanking.  (note I have no clue what HP will be reachable in PoP, just using those numbers to illustrate my point).<br>
<br>
Whatever they use to balance us needs to be something innate, not gear or buff dependent.<br>
